---
description: Apply backend domain and dependency rules to Python services
globs: "{apps/api,backend}/**/*.py"
alwaysApply: false
---

# Backend rules

- Keep domain code free of FastAPI, persistence, provider, scheduler, and LLM imports.
- Model lifecycle transitions explicitly and enforce invariants inside aggregates or domain policies.
- Application handlers coordinate ports and aggregates; they do not contain domain rules.
- Infrastructure adapters implement inward-owned protocols and are wired only at the composition root.
- Validate input at the boundary and return stable, intentional errors without leaking internals.
- Use type hints, deterministic behavior, UTC timestamps, and tests at the narrowest useful layer.
- Treat `backend/` as the legacy runtime until an approved migration slice moves capability to `apps/api/`.
